**Procédure :**
1. Afficher une modale de consentement au premier lancement
2. Stocker le choix dans AsyncStorage
3. Si consentement refusé, appeler `Analytics.setAnalyticsCollectionEnabled(false)`
4. Si accepté, `Analytics.setAnalyticsCollectionEnabled(true)`

**Code :**
```jsx
import * as Analytics from 'expo-firebase-analytics';
import AsyncStorage from '@react-native-async-storage/async-storage';

const initAnalytics = async () => {
  const consent = await AsyncStorage.getItem('analytics_consent');
  if (consent === 'granted') {
    await Analytics.setAnalyticsCollectionEnabled(true);
  } else if (consent === 'denied') {
    await Analytics.setAnalyticsCollectionEnabled(false);
  } else {
    // Afficher la modale de consentement
  }
};

const grantConsent = async () => {
  await AsyncStorage.setItem('analytics_consent', 'granted');
  await Analytics.setAnalyticsCollectionEnabled(true);
};

const denyConsent = async () => {
  await AsyncStorage.setItem('analytics_consent', 'denied');
  await Analytics.setAnalyticsCollectionEnabled(false);
};
```
